title: Grateful Dead Live at Des Moines Civic Center on 1981-12-07
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.6 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Bertha-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Friend Of The Devil-> CC Rider, Dire Wolf, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Deep Elem Blues, Cassidy, Althea, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Mississippi Half Step-> Franklin's Tower, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Nobody's Fault But Mine-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Don't Ease Me In

reviews.review_text: so cal to midwest  i read reviews for the story  no so much what some one thinks about the  how the show sounded to them  so here my story of my first  midwest tour  was young and fearless drove to dayton ohio the place was small i think a hockey  rink  good sound   des moines was the home town of stacy  our little sister  she she danced like a  twirling  gypsy  and was gust a good time  when we got to  champlain  ill  ran into jerry in lobby  of marriott  he took  the time to talk  i dident wana bother him but my friend  wanted his autograph   so why he signed i asked about the xx factor  he said something to the afeck that what we go for  we ended up geting  tickets  from  his  hotel waiter said he reading alot of ufo books  my x factor was  passenger  it gets stranger  afther the show we get in a  elevator  in hotel  door open  it bobby  two chicks  he says what floor  with his hand on the button  im frying  purple gel  talking about love in the air wanted party  with him he wasent  haveing  it  i guss  he dident wana share he had two  i told my son about this and he dident belive me  the  theater where small show up without  tickets  get in somehow  and go to place you never been  like a tiger in a trance   like to add  rest in peace to  Robert  hunter  who gave us all those  timeless  lyrics  run for the roses

Des Moines 81' This isn't one of the best of 81' but it's a pretty decent show .I wish Jerry was more dominant in the mix but hey.Highlights for me are TMNS and the second half of set 2 starting with Saint of Circumstance.

Winter '81: N7 Deep Elem, Althea, and TMNS - lyrical blunders and all - shine from the first set. Otherwise, unremarkable first. Weird mix. Takes some time to get settled in, Brent really high- too high- in mix, tbh, and seems generally out of whack. Another speedy Tower. Sailor->St. is excellent with cool Supplication Jam.
